justify: explanation singapores government said it had not issued any statement discouraging consumption of imports from the us health experts say there is insufficient evidence that covid19 can be transmitted to humans through food
label: Misleading
title: a claim states that singapore has banned people from buying fruit and vegetables imported from the us over fears it could be contaminated with the novel coronavirus the post goes on to allege the us has been transporting products in trucks that also carry dead bodies infected with covid19
author: Singapore Food Agency SFA
content: We are aware of posts circulating on social media making spurious claims that Singapore media has reported that fruits and food products exported from the United States US  Europe and Brazil to Asia and Africa have been contaminated by the COVID19 virus SFA has not issued any statement discouraging consumption of imports from the US  Europe or Brazil Neither has the Singapore media made such reports We are not aware of any evidence that suggests that the COVID19 virus can be transmitted to humans via food or food packaging and equipment This is the current state of knowledge across scientific communities and public health authorities worldwide SFA will continue to monitor developments closely and promptly take any necessary actions to safeguard food safety in Singapore The environment that we interact with can be easily contaminated with the COVID19 virus In general  contact with food or food packaging and equipment is no different from contact with other nonfood packaging and the environment eg common touch surfaces such as lift buttons  door knobs  etc As such  SFA continues to emphasise the importance of good public and personal hygiene practices to uphold a high level of public health standards in Singapore These include  Seeking medical attention promptly and staying home if unwell  Washing hands with soap and water regularly  including before eating and after going to the toilet  Cooking food thoroughly before eating  Avoid touching your face with your hands  Covering mouth and nose with a tissue when coughingsneezing  and throwing the tissue away into a bin immediately  Not engaging in any food handlingpreparation if unwell and  Not sharing fooddrinks with others
content_en: We are aware of posts circulating on social media making spurious claims that Singapore media has reported that fruits and food products exported from the United States US  Europe and Brazil to Asia and Africa have been contaminated by the COVID19 virus SFA has not issued any statement discouraging consumption of imports from the US  Europe or Brazil Neither has the Singapore media made such reports We are not aware of any evidence that suggests that the COVID19 virus can be transmitted to humans via food or food packaging and equipment This is the current state of knowledge across scientific communities and public health authorities worldwide SFA will continue to monitor developments closely and promptly take any necessary actions to safeguard food safety in Singapore The environment that we interact with can be easily contaminated with the COVID19 virus In general  contact with food or food packaging and equipment is no different from contact with other nonfood packaging and the environment eg common touch surfaces such as lift buttons  door knobs  etc As such  SFA continues to emphasise the importance of good public and personal hygiene practices to uphold a high level of public health standards in Singapore These include  Seeking medical attention promptly and staying home if unwell  Washing hands with soap and water regularly  including before eating and after going to the toilet  Cooking food thoroughly before eating  Avoid touching your face with your hands  Covering mouth and nose with a tissue when coughingsneezing  and throwing the tissue away into a bin immediately  Not engaging in any food handlingpreparation if unwell and  Not sharing fooddrinks with others

justify: explanation due to its reliability and relative ease of specimen collection  the nasopharyngeal swab is considered the goldstandard procedure for collecting cells and secretions from the back of the throat for covid19 diagnostic testing in contrast  the accuracy of less invasive testing of alternative specimens  such as saliva  is still under evaluation several laboratories have developed athome kits for the collection of nasal mucus and saliva samples that are then shipped to a laboratory for analysis however  specimen collection is a key step in clinical diagnosis  and experts have raised concerns about how potential flaws in athome sample collection may impact the accuracy of these tests
label: Misleading
title: using nasopharyngeal swabs for covid19 testing is unnecessary saliva samples from mouth swabs is an equivalent substitute

author: Partito Democratico
content: Democratic Party  Renzians and 5 Stelle have just voted AGAINST House Budget Committee the Leagues amendment that provided an economic prize for doctors  nurses and healthcare staff   Salvini cries on social media What do you do  not tickle the belly of the country by telling of a government deployed against those who are doing a huge job these past months in the fight against Covid Effective controversy actually If the news were true Right  because instead we are faced with yet another fake news circulated by a senator  Salvini  who continues to  fight  to remain on the podium of the biggest buffalarians of this period Yes  because the Government  in the Relaunch Decree  has in fact allocated 250 million down to the fund to remuneration for the activity carried out that goes beyond the overtime work done during the emergency And the regions with own resources are already allowed to use up to twice as many of these allocated resources Many have already predicted bonuses and prizes So an exhortation  Senator Salvini less lies Less cherries More real data People deserve the truth Chiara Braga
content_en: Democratic Party  Renzians and 5 Stelle have just voted AGAINST House Budget Committee the Leagues amendment that provided an economic prize for doctors  nurses and healthcare staff   Salvini cries on social media What do you do  not tickle the belly of the country by telling of a government deployed against those who are doing a huge job these past months in the fight against Covid Effective controversy actually If the news were true Right  because instead we are faced with yet another fake news circulated by a senator  Salvini  who continues to  fight  to remain on the podium of the biggest buffalarians of this period Yes  because the Government  in the Relaunch Decree  has in fact allocated 250 million down to the fund to remuneration for the activity carried out that goes beyond the overtime work done during the emergency And the regions with own resources are already allowed to use up to twice as many of these allocated resources Many have already predicted bonuses and prizes So an exhortation  Senator Salvini less lies Less cherries More real data People deserve the truth Chiara Braga

justify: explanation the title of the article on the portal of one television manipulatively presented the statement of geneticist and university professor from bih damir marjanoviÄ‡ about the origin of the sarscov2 virus  which he gave in the television program of the same media the manipulation added a tone of conspiracy theory to the statement and falsely claimed claim that the professor said that the virus may have been artificially spread  which he did not said after the reaction of professor marjanoviÄ‡  the title with the disputed claim was changed
label: MISLEADING
title: geneticist and bih university professor damir marjanovic says the new coronavirus may have been artificially spread
author: Prof dr Damir Marjanovi
content: There is now 15 years when we did a small genetic study and when we got interesting results for us scientists that fit into the paradigm of then European research But free interpretation of scientific data primarily related to headlines that didnt have much to do with what was said  back in 2005  taught me to be strong  I repeat very careful with media statements But those who did they seek sensation they try to find it where it is gone  and even when facts and words speak differently Before trusting a title  it would be good to listen to the whole interview and try to find at least one statement of this  allknown Marjanovic  who expressed his opinion that the virus is  artificial origin or agree that it was intentionally expanded  Responsible and professional journalists from N1 television whose professional approach I have so far convinced myself thousands of times have just respected and corrected the original title that could insinuate it  and thank them for that Maybe some other portals will follow this example As I said in the past post  such titles and real ones from scientists ad hoc conspiracy theorists  what is not wise to do at this time that marks information eruption  but disinformation But whats there  lets move on Nikola thank you for the invitation  I enjoyed the conversation and I look forward to another guest
content_en: There is now 15 years when we did a small genetic study and when we got interesting results for us scientists that fit into the paradigm of then European research But free interpretation of scientific data primarily related to headlines that didnt have much to do with what was said  back in 2005  taught me to be strong  I repeat very careful with media statements But those who did they seek sensation they try to find it where it is gone  and even when facts and words speak differently Before trusting a title  it would be good to listen to the whole interview and try to find at least one statement of this  allknown Marjanovic  who expressed his opinion that the virus is  artificial origin or agree that it was intentionally expanded  Responsible and professional journalists from N1 television whose professional approach I have so far convinced myself thousands of times have just respected and corrected the original title that could insinuate it  and thank them for that Maybe some other portals will follow this example As I said in the past post  such titles and real ones from scientists ad hoc conspiracy theorists  what is not wise to do at this time that marks information eruption  but disinformation But whats there  lets move on Nikola thank you for the invitation  I enjoyed the conversation and I look forward to another guest

and because the text is too medical to report an interesting testimony from an anatomy pathologist just think that Bergamos  Pope John XXIII  performed 50 autopsies and the  Sacco   of Milan 20 the Italian one is the highest case in the world  the Chinese have only done 3 and  minimally invasive  Everything that comes out seems to fully confirm the above information In a nutshell  it seems that exitus is determined by a DIC for nondoctors  Disseminated Intravascular Coagulation triggered by the virus So interstitial pneumonia had nothing to do with it  it was just a diagnostic mistake we doubled the places in CPR  with exorbitant costs  probably unnecessarily In hindsight  I think about all those Rx Torax we commented on about a month ago those images that were interstitial pneumonia might actually be completely consistent with an INTRAVASCULATED COAGULATION

author: Global Incident Tracking Report
content: 26 The diseased version of the new coronavirus gene tree in the United States has evolved the longest in the world with 26 mutations    3826 3218 22610 26 1026263  18321022648  The diseased version of the new coronavirus gene tree in the United States has evolved the longest in the world with 26 mutations When the world is fully fighting the epidemic  At the same time  there are many voices questioning where the source of the new crown virus is  and there is more and more evidence that Wuhan is not the original source of the virus This article is transferred from Weibo for everyones reference unconfirmed The number of virus mutations in the gene tree proves that the strain version of the United States has evolved the longest  France is second  and China cannot even enter the top three Figure 1 A strain of a March 8th case in Washington State  USA  had 26 mutationsthe original website estimated that this problem had been exposed and the problem has been deleted  but fortunately I have screenshots  I ca nt run  clear Clear Figure 2 Frances patient strain had 18 mutations on March 2 Figure 3 The furthest mutation in China Hong Kong patients had only 10 mutations on February 26 Conclusion The more genetic mutations  the longer the virus has existed and evolved The Washington state of the United States has evolved 26 times the longest version of the Chinese mutation The gene does not lie The virus originated in the United States Lets talk about it visually It is like that the original virus carrier was pangolin Suppose it transmitted the virus to the citizens of Wuhan Now all the Chinese cases have less than 10 mutations Now there are 26 mutations in the virus in an American patient  indicating that pangolin transmitted the virus to Americans 26 times earlier than China If the virus has evolved in Wuhan for 3 months  the virus has evolved in the United States for at least six months  Therefore  precisely because the virus began to evolve in the United States half a year ago  its early version may be weakly infectious  and the Wuhan version mutated into a severe infectious agent It now appears that the virus spread in Europe and even South America longer than China In view of the fact that the data in the United States has been changed  look at the data of the 18 mutations in France collected on March 2 and the data of 10 mutations in Hong Kong collected on February 26  which is 4 days behind This shows that the French virus has evolved more than 8 mutations Why is there less foreign data on the roots of gene trees Because of the late screening of viruses in foreign countries  patients with very early versions of foreign strains have either died or been treated as colds The Chinese version of the strain has evolved far

justify: explanation dettol has been tested and found to kill coronaviruses such as middle east respiratory syndrome mers and severe acute respiratory syndrome sars however  the manufacturer of dettol  reckitt benckiser group plcrb  says it has not yet tested its products on the novel coronavirus and could not confirm whether dettol is effective against the new coronavirus strain
label: Misleading
title: dettol sanitizer can kill the coronavirus
author: Dettol UK
content: 31st January 2020  Slough  UK  RB has become aware of speculation about Dettol products and the novel 2019nCoV coronavirus As this is an emerging outbreak RB  like all manufacturers  doesnt yet have access to the new virus 2019nCoV for testing and  as a result  are not yet in a position to confirm levels of effectiveness against the new strain Our products have been tested against other coronaviruses such as MERSCoV and SARSCoV and have been found to kill those Although 2019nCoV is a new strain  this virus is very similar to other coronaviruses We continue to work with our partners to ensure that we have the latest understanding of the virus  route of transmission and will test our product range once health authorities make the strain available As a global leader in health and hygiene  we continue to play our part in combating and containing the outbreak of the virus To this end  we have donated 55 million in cash and products to assist in the mobilisation of medical staff to treat those affected and provide soap and hand sanitisers to hospitals in Wuhan to help contain the further spread of the virus It is vital the accurate  evidencedbased information is conveyed to the public so they are properly informed about the importance of good hygiene at all times  but particularly during outbreaks

justify: explanation the claim that the new coronavirus was known beforehand on a clorox label shows that it kills human coronavirus is misleading
label: Misleading
title: clorox already knew about coronavirus and coronavirus isnt a new virus
author: Cheryl Robinson
content: A friend of mine checked the back of her Clorox wipes and  what do you know  the human coronavirus is listed among the things that these wipes kill I checked our wipes and  sure enough  it is listed So my take is  as I suspected  this is no NEW VIRUS as the news media wants us to believe
